y could be the recurrent structure in some Christian epitaphs from Syracuse, in which  is followed by the name of the deceased in genitive (see Korhonen 2002: 76-77). However, the first interpretation suggested by Korhonen is preferable, given the comparison with the other inscription from Catania that seems to present the same form. In the first case, the name of the deceased would be  (i.e. ) or in the feminine form  (both names, however, have no attestation in Sicily), in the second case, the genitive  could be integrated (Mercurelli and Ferrua had already suggested , attested only in an inscription from Aphrodisias of the V-VI century CE, IAph2007 15.363 l. 10).",{"_":464,"target":465},"ISic003506","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003506",[467,469,471,472,474,476,478,480],{"_":468,"xml:lang":101},"μνημεῖον",{"_":470,"xml:lang":101},"ἐνθάδε κεῖται",{"_":468,"xml:lang":101},{"_":473,"xml:lang":101},"Θεοχάρις",{"_":475,"xml:lang":101},"Θεοχάρης",{"_":477,"xml:lang":101},"Θεόχαρις",{"_":479,"xml:lang":101},"Θεοχαρ|ίστ[ου]",{"_":481,"xml:lang":101},"Θεοχαρίστος",{"type":483,"listBibl":484},"bibliography",[485,496],{"type":104,"bibl":486},[487,490,493],{"type":107,"n":108,"citedRange":109,"ptr":488,"ref":489},{"target":111},{"_":113,"target":113},{"type":115,"n":116,"author":117,"title":116,"date":118,"citedRange":119,"ptr":491,"ref":492},{"target":121},{"_":123,"target":123},{"author":117,"date":125,"citedRange":126,"ptr":494,"ref":495},{"target":128},{"_":130,"target":130},{"type":132,"bibl":497},{"author":134,"date":135,"citedRange":136,"ptr":498,"ref":499},{"target":138},{"_":140,"target":140},[501],{"n":383,"url":91,"height":384,"width":385,"desc":92,"surfaceType":380},{"title":503,"body":504,"divs":505,"images":521},"ISic003293. Fragment of an Epitaph","  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003293_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic003293_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003293.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic003293-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"edition\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div\">\u003Ca id=\"al1\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[[cross_latin]]ΜΝΗΜ[..........?....?]\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">ΘΕΟΧΑΡ\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΙΣΤ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">ΟΥΔ\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al3\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">line.1: \u003Cspan>Ferrua saw a Christogram with a small Σ in rasura\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">\u003Cspan>Libertini: μνήμ(η); Mercurelli, Ferrua, Korhonen: μνημ[εῖον]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">\u003Cspan>Korhonen: [ἔνθαδε κῖτε(?)]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"lines 1-2\">lines.1-2: \u003Cspan>Libertini, Mercurelli: ΘΕΟΥΧΑΡ|ΙΣΤ (i.e. θεοῦ χάριν); Ferrua: ΘΕΟΧΑΡ|ΙΣΤ (i.e. Θεοχαρ|ίστ[ος]); Korhonen: Θεοχάρ|ις (i.e. Θεοχάρης)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Tomb. Here lies Theochares …\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Sepolcro. Qui giace Theochares…\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The epitaph must have been Christian as revealed by the erased cross and the formula, characteristic of another Christian inscription found at the same cemetery in Via Dottor Consoli and published by Manganaro (Minima Epigraphica et papyrologica 5 (2001), 138 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003506\" target=\"_blank\">ISic003506\u003C/a>), in which the \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">μνημεῖον\u003C/span> is followed by the formula \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἐνθάδε κεῖται\u003C/span> and the nominative of the name of the deceased. Another possibility could be the recurrent structure in some Christian epitaphs from Syracuse, in which \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">μνημεῖον\u003C/span> is followed by the name of the deceased in genitive (see Korhonen 2002: 76-77). However, the first interpretation suggested by Korhonen is preferable, given the comparison with the other inscription from Catania that seems to present the same form. In the first case, the name of the deceased would be \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Θεοχάρις\u003C/span> (i.e. \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Θεοχάρης\u003C/span>) or in the feminine form \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Θεόχαρις\u003C/span> (both names, however, have no attestation in Sicily), in the second case, the genitive \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Θεοχαρ|ίστ[ου]\u003C/span> could be integrated (Mercurelli and Ferrua had already suggested \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Θεοχαρίστος\u003C/span>, attested only in an inscription from Aphrodisias of the V-VI century CE, IAph2007 15.363 l. 10).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> 198 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Libertini NSA 1937 77.b \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Libertini 1981 124 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001863\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001863\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> Korhonen 2002 76-77 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001898\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001898\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[506,508,510,512,514,516,518],{"id":104,"html":507},"\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div\">\u003Ca id=\"al1\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[[cross_latin]]ΜΝΗΜ[..........?....?]\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">ΘΕΟΧΑΡ\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΙΣΤ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">ΟΥΔ\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al3\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"id":439,"html":509},"\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">line.1: \u003Cspan>Ferrua saw a Christogram with a small Σ in rasura\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">\u003Cspan>Libertini: μνήμ(η); Mercurelli, Ferrua, Korhonen: μνημ[εῖον]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan cl